==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peanut
<hw>Pea"nut</hw> <pr>(p⟦emac⟧"n⟦ucr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The fruit of a trailing leguminous plant
(<spn>Arachis hypog⟦ae⟧a</spn>); also, the plant itself, which is widely
cultivated for its fruit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The fruit is a hard pod, usually containing two or three
seeds, sometimes but one, which ripen beneath the soil. Called also
<altname>earthnut</altname>, <altname>groundnut</altname>, and
<altname>goober</altname>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peanut butter</ent>⟦br⟧
